This paper is primarily focused on the optimization of Deep Neural Network (DNN) execution on mobile devices, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a novel model compression technique and architecture-aware compiler optimizations, which could also be relevant to the categories of robotics (cs.RO) and embedded systems (cs.ET). Finally, the paper mentions the use of real-time performance, which could be relevant to the category of control systems (cs.SY).
